examples.en: The wheel turns round.
Dan and I usually take turns to cook.
We take turns on the night shift.
His face turns red when he gets angry.
Much turns on his answer.
His luck improves / turns.
The sofa turns into a bed.
The wheel squeaks when it turns.
The road is full of abrupt turns.
Further on, the river turns east.
He turns everyone against himself.
Our brew of beer turns out excellent.
When water turns to steam, it expands.
He held out by turns coaxes and threats.
Everything he touches turns to disaster.
The pressure of the water turns the wheel.
I gave the screw another two or three turns.
The students were taking turns reading aloud.
If it turns fine, I shall put the washing out.
The road turns sharply at the top of the hill.
As the gear rotates, it turns the other gears.
He always turns first to the business section.
Roger never turns down an invitation to dinner.
Litmus paper turns red on contact with an acid.
Iago's lie is the pivot on which the play turns.
Paper-money is the pivot, on which their all turns.
The river twists and turns through the green fields.
The hottest salesman always turns a looker into an up.
What if the car you buy turns out to be a pig in a poke?
The dancer dazzled the audience with his turns and jumps
